{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1293,"text":"I'm a gamer, so I like to have goals."},{"time":5126,"text":"I like special missions\nand secret objectives."},{"time":9330,"text":"So here's my special mission\nfor this talk:"},{"time":13021,"text":"I'm going to try to increase the life span\nof every single person in this room"},{"time":17795,"text":"by seven and a half minutes."},{"time":20394,"text":"Literally, you will live seven\nand a half minutes longer"},{"time":23126,"text":"than you would have otherwise,"},{"time":24601,"text":"just because you watched this talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27554,"text":"Some of you are looking\na little bit skeptical."},{"time":29774,"text":"That's okay, because check it out --"},{"time":31514,"text":"I have math to prove that it is possible."},{"time":34291,"text":"It won't make much sense now."},{"time":35788,"text":"I'll explain it all later,"},{"time":37124,"text":"just pay attention\nto the number at the bottom:"},{"time":39387,"text":"+7.68245837 minutes."},{"time":42687,"text":"That will be my gift to you\nif I'm successful in my mission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46206,"text":"Now, you have a secret mission too."},{"time":49399,"text":"Your mission is to figure out\nhow you want to spend"},{"time":52934,"text":"your extra seven and a half minutes."},{"time":54998,"text":"And I think you should do\nsomething unusual with them,"},{"time":57570,"text":"because these are bonus minutes."},{"time":59124,"text":"You weren't going to have them anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61116,"text":"Now, because I'm a game designer,\nyou might be thinking to yourself,"},{"time":65140,"text":"I know what she wants us to do\nwith those minutes,"},{"time":67585,"text":"she wants us to spend them playing games."},{"time":69736,"text":"Now this is a totally\nreasonable assumption,"},{"time":72222,"text":"given that I have made quite\na habit of encouraging people"},{"time":75008,"text":"to spend more time playing games."},{"time":76654,"text":"For example, in my first TED Talk,"},{"time":78934,"text":"I did propose that we should spend\n21 billion hours a week,"},{"time":83125,"text":"as a planet, playing video games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85246,"text":"Now, 21 billion hours, it's a lot of time."},{"time":88633,"text":"It's so much time, in fact,\nthat the number one unsolicited comment"},{"time":92967,"text":"that I have heard from people\nall over the world"},{"time":95269,"text":"since I gave that talk, is this:"},{"time":97938,"text":"Jane, games are great and all,\nbut on your deathbed,"},{"time":101460,"text":"are you really going to wish you spent\nmore time playing Angry Birds?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104981,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":106005,"text":"This idea is so pervasive --"},{"time":108154,"text":"that games are a waste of time\nthat we will come to regret --"},{"time":111072,"text":"that I hear it literally everywhere I go."},{"time":113245,"text":"For example, true story:"},{"time":115164,"text":"Just a few weeks ago,"},{"time":116528,"text":"this cab driver, upon finding out\nthat a friend and I were in town"},{"time":119878,"text":"for a game developers' conference,"},{"time":121791,"text":"turned around and said -- and I quote --"},{"time":124886,"text":"\"I hate games. Waste of life."},{"time":127476,"text":"Imagine getting to the end of your life\nand regretting all that time.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":132734,"text":"Now, I want to take\nthis problem seriously."},{"time":135353,"text":"I want games to be\na force for good in the world."},{"time":137908,"text":"I don't want gamers to regret\nthe time they spent playing,"},{"time":140708,"text":"time that I encouraged them to spend."},{"time":142834,"text":"So I have been thinking about this\nquestion a lot lately."},{"time":146468,"text":"When we're on our deathbeds,"},{"time":148280,"text":"will we regret the time\nwe spent playing games?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151899,"text":"Now, this may surprise you,\nbut it turns out"},{"time":154414,"text":"there is actually some scientific research\non this question."},{"time":157582,"text":"It's true."},{"time":158855,"text":"Hospice workers,"},{"time":160470,"text":"the people who take care of us\nat the end of our lives,"},{"time":163405,"text":"recently issued a report\non the most frequently expressed regrets"},{"time":168206,"text":"that people say when they are\nliterally on their deathbeds."},{"time":172407,"text":"And that's what I want\nto share with you today --"},{"time":174725,"text":"the top five regrets of the dying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178810,"text":"Number one:"},{"time":180900,"text":"I wish I hadn't worked so hard."},{"time":185798,"text":"Number two:"},{"time":187458,"text":"I wish I had stayed\nin touch with my friends."},{"time":191346,"text":"Number three:"},{"time":192501,"text":"I wish I had let myself be happier."},{"time":197722,"text":"Number four:"},{"time":198933,"text":"I wish I'd had the courage\nto express my true self."},{"time":203824,"text":"And number five:"},{"time":205293,"text":"I wish I'd lived a life true to my dreams,"},{"time":208001,"text":"instead of what others expected of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212105,"text":"Now, as far as I know, no one ever\ntold one of the hospice workers,"},{"time":215611,"text":"\"I wish I'd spent more\ntime playing video games,\""},{"time":218706,"text":"but when I hear these top five\nregrets of the dying,"},{"time":221310,"text":"I can't help but hear\nfive deep human cravings"},{"time":224126,"text":"that games actually help us fulfill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226150,"text":"For example, I wish\nI hadn't worked so hard."},{"time":228845,"text":"For many people, this means,\nI wish I'd spent more time"},{"time":231576,"text":"with my family, with my kids\nwhen they were growing up."},{"time":234289,"text":"Well, we know that playing games together\nhas tremendous family benefits."},{"time":238462,"text":"A recent study from Brigham\nYoung University School of Family Life"},{"time":241884,"text":"reported that parents who spend more time\nplaying video games with their kids"},{"time":246131,"text":"have much stronger\nreal-life relationships with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250810,"text":"\"I wish I'd stayed in touch\nwith my friends.\""},{"time":253426,"text":"Hundreds of millions of people"},{"time":254894,"text":"use social games like FarmVille\nor Words With Friends"},{"time":258056,"text":"to stay in daily contact\nwith real-life friends and family."},{"time":261385,"text":"A recent study from\nthe University of Michigan"},{"time":264877,"text":"showed that these games are incredibly\npowerful relationship-management tools."},{"time":271598,"text":"They help us stay connected\nwith people in our social network"},{"time":275433,"text":"that we would otherwise grow distant from,"},{"time":277553,"text":"if we weren't playing games together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279853,"text":"\"I wish I'd let myself be happier.\""},{"time":281670,"text":"Well, here I can't help but think\nof the groundbreaking clinical trials"},{"time":285075,"text":"recently conducted\nat East Carolina University"},{"time":288003,"text":"that showed that online games\ncan outperform"},{"time":290878,"text":"pharmaceuticals for treating\nclinical anxiety and depression."},{"time":295135,"text":"Just 30 minutes of online game play a day"},{"time":298151,"text":"was enough to create\ndramatic boosts in mood"},{"time":301148,"text":"and long-term increases in happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305545,"text":"\"I wish I'd had the courage\nto express my true self.\""},{"time":308204,"text":"Well, avatars are a way\nto express our true selves,"},{"time":311862,"text":"our most heroic, idealized\nversion of who we might become."},{"time":315218,"text":"You can see that in this alter ego\nportrait by Robbie Cooper"},{"time":318860,"text":"of a gamer with his avatar."},{"time":321360,"text":"And Stanford University has been\ndoing research for five years now"},{"time":324854,"text":"to document how playing a game\nwith an idealized avatar"},{"time":329031,"text":"changes how we think and act in real life,"},{"time":331825,"text":"making us more courageous, more ambitious,"},{"time":334809,"text":"more committed to our goals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338452,"text":"\"I wish I'd led a life true to my dreams,"},{"time":340568,"text":"and not what others expected of me.\""},{"time":342398,"text":"Are games doing this yet?"},{"time":343704,"text":"I'm not sure, so I've left\na Super Mario question mark."},{"time":347204,"text":"We're going to come back to this one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349545,"text":"But in the meantime,\nperhaps you're wondering,"},{"time":353085,"text":"who is this game designer\nto be talking to us"},{"time":356044,"text":"about deathbed regrets?"},{"time":357856,"text":"And it's true, I've never\nworked in a hospice,"},{"time":361237,"text":"I've never been on my deathbed."},{"time":364150,"text":"But recently I did spend\nthree months in bed, wanting to die."},{"time":370356,"text":"Really wanting to die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372236,"text":"Now let me tell you that story."},{"time":374617,"text":"It started two years ago, when I hit\nmy head and got a concussion."},{"time":377745,"text":"The concussion didn't heal properly,"},{"time":379542,"text":"and after 30 days, I was left\nwith symptoms like nonstop headaches,"},{"time":383323,"text":"nausea, vertigo, memory loss, mental fog."},{"time":386645,"text":"My doctor told me that in order\nto heal my brain,"},{"time":389073,"text":"I had to rest it."},{"time":390121,"text":"So I had to avoid everything\nthat triggered my symptoms."},{"time":392778,"text":"For me that meant no reading,\nno writing, no video games,"},{"time":395673,"text":"no work or email, no running,\nno alcohol, no caffeine."},{"time":398753,"text":"In other words -- and I think\nyou see where this is going --"},{"time":401746,"text":"no reason to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402850,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":403875,"text":"Of course it's meant to be funny,"},{"time":405740,"text":"but in all seriousness,\nsuicidal ideation is quite common"},{"time":409658,"text":"with traumatic brain injuries."},{"time":411621,"text":"It happens to one in three,\nand it happened to me."},{"time":415243,"text":"My brain started telling me,\n\"Jane, you want to die.\""},{"time":420421,"text":"It said, \"You're never going\nto get better.\""},{"time":423797,"text":"It said, \"The pain will never end.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":427384,"text":"And these voices became\nso persistent and so persuasive"},{"time":431566,"text":"that I started to legitimately\nfear for my life,"},{"time":436699,"text":"which is the time that I said\nto myself after 34 days --"},{"time":441200,"text":"and I will never forget this moment --"},{"time":443287,"text":"I said, \"I am either going to kill myself"},{"time":446694,"text":"or I'm going to turn this into a game.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":449321,"text":"Now, why a game?"},{"time":450490,"text":"I knew from researching the psychology\nof games for more than a decade"},{"time":454618,"text":"that when we play a game --"},{"time":456349,"text":"and this is\nin the scientific literature --"},{"time":458404,"text":"we tackle tough challenges\nwith more creativity,"},{"time":461197,"text":"more determination, more optimism,"},{"time":462898,"text":"and we're more likely\nto reach out to others for help."},{"time":465470,"text":"I wanted to bring these gamer traits\nto my real-life challenge,"},{"time":468513,"text":"so I created a role-playing recovery game"},{"time":470533,"text":"called Jane the Concussion Slayer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472441,"text":"Now this became my new secret identity,"},{"time":475259,"text":"and the first thing I did as a slayer\nwas call my twin sister --"},{"time":478683,"text":"I have an identical\ntwin sister named Kelly --"},{"time":481015,"text":"and tell her, \"I'm playing\na game to heal my brain,"},{"time":484757,"text":"and I want you to play with me.\""},{"time":486829,"text":"This was an easier way to ask for help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490887,"text":"She became my first ally in the game,"},{"time":493149,"text":"my husband Kiyash joined next,"},{"time":495109,"text":"and together we identified\nand battled the bad guys."},{"time":498527,"text":"Now this was anything\nthat could trigger my symptoms"},{"time":501639,"text":"and therefore slow down\nthe healing process,"},{"time":503727,"text":"things like bright lights\nand crowded spaces."},{"time":506099,"text":"We also collected and activated power-ups."},{"time":509144,"text":"This was anything I could do\non even my worst day"},{"time":512105,"text":"to feel just a little bit good,"},{"time":514272,"text":"just a little bit productive."},{"time":516200,"text":"Things like cuddling\nmy dog for 10 minutes,"},{"time":518917,"text":"or getting out of bed and walking\naround the block just once."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522209,"text":"Now the game was that simple:"},{"time":523973,"text":"Adopt a secret identity,\nrecruit your allies,"},{"time":527131,"text":"battle the bad guys,\nactivate the power-ups."},{"time":530155,"text":"But even with a game so simple,"},{"time":532139,"text":"within just a couple days\nof starting to play,"},{"time":534702,"text":"that fog of depression\nand anxiety went away."},{"time":538533,"text":"It just vanished. It felt like a miracle."},{"time":540993,"text":"Now it wasn't a miracle cure\nfor the headaches"},{"time":543505,"text":"or the cognitive symptoms."},{"time":544768,"text":"That lasted for more than a year,"},{"time":546509,"text":"and it was the hardest year\nof my life by far."},{"time":549699,"text":"But even when I still had the symptoms,"},{"time":552033,"text":"even while I was still in pain,\nI stopped suffering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556723,"text":"Now what happened next\nwith the game surprised me."},{"time":559199,"text":"I put up some blog posts\nand videos online,"},{"time":561284,"text":"explaining how to play."},{"time":562729,"text":"But not everybody\nhas a concussion, obviously,"},{"time":565284,"text":"not everyone wants to be \"the slayer,\""},{"time":567540,"text":"so I renamed the game SuperBetter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570240,"text":"And soon, I started hearing\nfrom people all over the world"},{"time":573470,"text":"who were adopting\ntheir own secret identity,"},{"time":575780,"text":"recruiting their own allies,\nand they were getting \"super better,\""},{"time":579105,"text":"facing challenges\nlike cancer and chronic pain,"},{"time":583011,"text":"depression and Crohn's disease."},{"time":585344,"text":"Even people were playing it\nfor terminal diagnoses like ALS."},{"time":589725,"text":"And I could tell from their messages\nand their videos"},{"time":593368,"text":"that the game was helping them\nin the same ways that it helped me."},{"time":596955,"text":"They talked about feeling\nstronger and braver."},{"time":600286,"text":"They talked about feeling better\nunderstood by their friends and family."},{"time":604516,"text":"And they even talked\nabout feeling happier,"},{"time":607083,"text":"even though they were in pain,"},{"time":609187,"text":"even though they were tackling\nthe toughest challenge of their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612578,"text":"Now at the time, I'm thinking\nto myself, what is going on here?"},{"time":616463,"text":"I mean, how could a game\nso trivial intervene so powerfully"},{"time":621380,"text":"in such serious, and in some cases\nlife-and-death, circumstances?"},{"time":625331,"text":"I mean, if it hadn't worked for me,"},{"time":627126,"text":"there's no way I would have\nbelieved it was possible."},{"time":629657,"text":"Well, it turns out\nthere's some science here, too."},{"time":633141,"text":"Some people get stronger and happier\nafter a traumatic event."},{"time":637863,"text":"And that's what was happening to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639680,"text":"The game was helping us experience"},{"time":641825,"text":"what scientists call\npost-traumatic growth,"},{"time":644979,"text":"which is not something\nwe usually hear about."},{"time":647203,"text":"We usually hear about\npost-traumatic stress disorder."},{"time":650092,"text":"But scientists now know\nthat a traumatic event"},{"time":652708,"text":"doesn't doom us to suffer indefinitely."},{"time":655598,"text":"Instead, we can use it as a springboard"},{"time":657962,"text":"to unleash our best qualities\nand lead happier lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661482,"text":"Here are the top five things that people\nwith post-traumatic growth say:"},{"time":666148,"text":"\"My priorities have changed.\""},{"time":667696,"text":"\"I'm not afraid to do\nwhat makes me happy.\""},{"time":670553,"text":"\"I feel closer to my friends and family.\""},{"time":673823,"text":"\"I understand myself better.\nI know who I really am now.\""},{"time":677863,"text":"\"I have a new sense of meaning\nand purpose in my life.\""},{"time":681414,"text":"\"I'm better able to focus\non my goals and dreams.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":684454,"text":"Now, does this sound familiar?"},{"time":686573,"text":"It should, because the top five traits\nof post-traumatic growth"},{"time":690829,"text":"are essentially the direct opposite\nof the top five regrets of the dying."},{"time":696343,"text":"Now this is interesting, right?"},{"time":697907,"text":"It seems that somehow, a traumatic event"},{"time":700627,"text":"can unlock our ability to lead\na life with fewer regrets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704791,"text":"But how does it work?"},{"time":706111,"text":"How do you get from trauma to growth?"},{"time":708656,"text":"Or better yet, is there a way\nto get all the benefits"},{"time":711431,"text":"of post-traumatic growth\nwithout the trauma,"},{"time":713952,"text":"without having to hit\nyour head in the first place?"},{"time":716405,"text":"That would be good, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":717912,"text":"I wanted to understand\nthe phenomenon better,"},{"time":720311,"text":"so I devoured the scientific literature,\nand here's what I learned."},{"time":723867,"text":"There are four kinds\nof strength, or resilience,"},{"time":726743,"text":"that contribute to post-traumatic growth,"},{"time":729883,"text":"and there are scientifically\nvalidated activities"},{"time":732481,"text":"that you can do every day to build up\nthese four kinds of resilience,"},{"time":736945,"text":"and you don't need a trauma to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738738,"text":"I could tell you what these four\ntypes of strength are,"},{"time":741348,"text":"but I'd rather you\nexperience them firsthand."},{"time":743475,"text":"I'd rather we all start building them up\ntogether right now."},{"time":746448,"text":"Here's what we're going to do."},{"time":747903,"text":"We'll play a quick game together."},{"time":749704,"text":"This is where you earn\nthe seven and a half minutes"},{"time":752127,"text":"of bonus life that I promised you earlier."},{"time":754151,"text":"All you have to do\nis successfully complete"},{"time":756822,"text":"the first four SuperBetter quests."},{"time":759163,"text":"And I feel like you can do it.\nI have confidence in you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761829,"text":"So, everybody ready?"},{"time":763213,"text":"This is your first quest. Here we go."},{"time":765500,"text":"Pick one: Stand up and take three steps,"},{"time":768256,"text":"or make your hands into fists,\nraise them over your head"},{"time":770922,"text":"as high as you can for five seconds, go!"},{"time":774704,"text":"All right, I like the people doing both."},{"time":776713,"text":"You are overachievers. Very good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778342,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":779435,"text":"Well done, everyone."},{"time":780482,"text":"That is worth +1 physical resilience,"},{"time":782642,"text":"which means that your body\ncan withstand more stress"},{"time":785388,"text":"and heal itself faster."},{"time":786927,"text":"We know from the research"},{"time":788262,"text":"that the number one thing you can do\nto boost your physical resilience"},{"time":791652,"text":"is to not sit still."},{"time":792952,"text":"That's all it takes."},{"time":794176,"text":"Every single second\nthat you are not sitting still,"},{"time":797396,"text":"you are actively improving\nthe health of your heart,"},{"time":800188,"text":"and your lungs and brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801806,"text":"Everybody ready for your next quest?"},{"time":804180,"text":"I want you to snap\nyour fingers exactly 50 times,"},{"time":806497,"text":"or count backwards from 100\nby seven, like this: 100, 93..."},{"time":810024,"text":"Go!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":811061,"text":"(Snapping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":814513,"text":"Don't give up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815600,"text":"(Snapping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":818415,"text":"Don't let the people\ncounting down from 100"},{"time":820471,"text":"interfere with your counting to 50."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822201,"text":"(Snapping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":825113,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":826686,"text":"Nice. Wow. That's the first\ntime I've ever seen that."},{"time":830414,"text":"Bonus physical resilience.\nWell done, everyone."},{"time":833390,"text":"Now that's worth +1 mental resilience,"},{"time":835500,"text":"which means you have more\nmental focus, more discipline,"},{"time":838191,"text":"determination and willpower."},{"time":840041,"text":"We know from the scientific research"},{"time":841853,"text":"that willpower\nactually works like a muscle."},{"time":844004,"text":"It gets stronger the more you exercise it."},{"time":846779,"text":"So tackling a tiny challenge\nwithout giving up,"},{"time":850155,"text":"even one as absurd as snapping\nyour fingers exactly 50 times"},{"time":853537,"text":"or counting backwards from 100 by seven"},{"time":855419,"text":"is actually a scientifically validated way\nto boost your willpower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859015,"text":"So good job. Quest number three."},{"time":861017,"text":"Pick one: Because of the room,\nfate's really determined this for you,"},{"time":864305,"text":"but here are the two options."},{"time":865713,"text":"If you're inside,\nfind a window and look out of it."},{"time":868191,"text":"If you're outside,\nfind a window and look in."},{"time":870743,"text":"Or do a quick YouTube\nor Google image search"},{"time":873368,"text":"for \"baby [your favorite animal.]\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":875164,"text":"Do it on your phones,\nor just shout out some baby animals,"},{"time":877989,"text":"and I'll put them on the screen."},{"time":879565,"text":"So, what do we want to see?"},{"time":881045,"text":"Sloth, giraffe, elephant, snake.\nOkay, let's see what we got."},{"time":886522,"text":"Baby dolphin and baby llamas.\nEverybody look."},{"time":891775,"text":"Got that?"},{"time":893017,"text":"Okay, one more. Baby elephant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895272,"text":"(Audience) Oh!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896461,"text":"We're clapping for that?"},{"time":897946,"text":"That's amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899154,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":900270,"text":"All right, what we're just feeling there\nis plus-one emotional resilience,"},{"time":903793,"text":"which means you have the ability\nto provoke powerful,"},{"time":906319,"text":"positive emotions like curiosity or love,"},{"time":908801,"text":"which we feel looking at baby animals,"},{"time":910677,"text":"when you need them most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911928,"text":"Here's a secret from the scientific\nliterature for you."},{"time":914606,"text":"If you can manage to experience\nthree positive emotions"},{"time":918331,"text":"for every one negative emotion"},{"time":920856,"text":"over the course of an hour, a day, a week,"},{"time":923848,"text":"you dramatically improve your health"},{"time":925944,"text":"and your ability to successfully tackle\nany problem you're facing."},{"time":929528,"text":"And this is called the three-to-one\npositive emotion ratio."},{"time":932807,"text":"It's my favorite\nSuperBetter trick, so keep it up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935489,"text":"All right, pick one, last quest:"},{"time":937584,"text":"Shake someone's hand for six seconds,"},{"time":939440,"text":"or send someone a quick thank you"},{"time":941171,"text":"by text, email, Facebook or Twitter. Go!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":943101,"text":"(Chatting)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":948069,"text":"Looking good, looking good."},{"time":951486,"text":"Nice, nice."},{"time":953565,"text":"Keep it up."},{"time":955347,"text":"I love it!"},{"time":956372,"text":"All right, everybody,\nthat is +1 social resilience,"},{"time":959788,"text":"which means you actually get\nmore strength from your friends,"},{"time":963035,"text":"your neighbors, your family,\nyour community."},{"time":965156,"text":"Now, a great way to boost\nsocial resilience is gratitude."},{"time":968665,"text":"Touch is even better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":969956,"text":"Here's one more secret for you:"},{"time":971507,"text":"Shaking someone's hand for six seconds"},{"time":973776,"text":"dramatically raises the level\nof oxytocin in your bloodstream,"},{"time":976812,"text":"now that's the trust hormone."},{"time":978678,"text":"That means that all of you\nwho just shook hands"},{"time":980927,"text":"are biochemically primed to like\nand want to help each other."},{"time":984339,"text":"This will linger during the break,"},{"time":986891,"text":"so take advantage\nof the networking opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989301,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":990371,"text":"Well, you have successfully\ncompleted your four quests,"},{"time":993101,"text":"let's see if I've successfully\ncompleted my mission"},{"time":995528,"text":"to give you seven and a half\nminutes of bonus life."},{"time":997937,"text":"Now I get to share one more\nlittle bit of science with you."},{"time":1000762,"text":"It turns out that people who regularly\nboost these four types of resilience --"},{"time":1004946,"text":"physical, mental, emotional and social --"},{"time":1007485,"text":"live 10 years longer than everyone else."},{"time":1009942,"text":"So this is true."},{"time":1011028,"text":"If you are regularly achieving\nthe three-to-one positive emotion ratio,"},{"time":1014835,"text":"if you are never sitting still\nfor more than an hour at a time,"},{"time":1017986,"text":"if you are reaching out to one person\nyou care about every single day,"},{"time":1021855,"text":"if you are tackling tiny goals\nto boost your willpower,"},{"time":1025982,"text":"you will live 10 years longer\nthan everyone else,"},{"time":1028333,"text":"and here's where that math\nI showed you earlier comes in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031072,"text":"So, the average life expectancy\nin the U.S. and the U.K. is 78.1 years,"},{"time":1035095,"text":"but we know from more than 1,000\npeer-reviewed scientific studies"},{"time":1038223,"text":"that you can add 10 years of life\nby boosting your four types of resilience."},{"time":1041842,"text":"So every single year that you are boosting\nyour four types of resilience,"},{"time":1045401,"text":"you're actually earning\n.128 more years of life"},{"time":1047674,"text":"or 46 more days of life,\nor 67,298 more minutes of life,"},{"time":1052247,"text":"which means every single day,\nyou are earning 184 minutes of life,"},{"time":1056561,"text":"or every single hour that you are boosting\nyour four types of resilience,"},{"time":1060062,"text":"like we just did together,\nyou are earning 7.68245837"},{"time":1063327,"text":"more minutes of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064422,"text":"Congratulations, those seven\nand a half minutes are all yours."},{"time":1067358,"text":"You totally earned them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068858,"text":"Yeah!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069889,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1071207,"text":"Awesome."},{"time":1073034,"text":"Wait, wait, wait."},{"time":1075649,"text":"You still have your special mission,\nyour secret mission."},{"time":1078804,"text":"How are you going to spend\nthese minutes of bonus life?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081868,"text":"Well, here's my suggestion."},{"time":1083585,"text":"These seven and a half bonus minutes\nare kind of like genie's wishes."},{"time":1087227,"text":"You can use your first wish\nto wish for a million more wishes."},{"time":1090725,"text":"Pretty clever, right?"},{"time":1091796,"text":"So, if you spend these\nseven and a half minutes today"},{"time":1095651,"text":"doing something that makes you happy,"},{"time":1098285,"text":"or that gets you physically active,"},{"time":1100028,"text":"or puts you in touch\nwith someone you care about,"},{"time":1103131,"text":"or even just tackling a tiny challenge,"},{"time":1105964,"text":"you're going to boost your resilience,\nso you're going to earn more minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109613,"text":"And the good news is,\nyou can keep going like that."},{"time":1112092,"text":"Every hour of the day,\nevery day of your life,"},{"time":1114396,"text":"all the way to your deathbed,"},{"time":1115828,"text":"which will now be 10 years later\nthan it would have otherwise."},{"time":1119081,"text":"And when you get there, more than likely,"},{"time":1122263,"text":"you will not have\nany of those top five regrets,"},{"time":1125803,"text":"because you will have built up\nthe strength and resilience"},{"time":1128676,"text":"to lead a life truer to your dreams."},{"time":1132136,"text":"And with 10 extra years,\nyou might even have enough time"},{"time":1135399,"text":"to play a few more games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1137342,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1138445,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}